block.comment: This block gives a number code for any character. The letter "a" is 97, the letter "b" is 98, the letter "c" is 99...etc. We made the user's input lower case above because Upper case letters have different codes than lower case ones.
If you subtract 96 from the code given by the unicode of block, you can convert a letter to it's position in the alphabet.
